cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image processing algorithms and specifically focuses on distributions of angular quantities. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new kernel that allows for kernel density estimation, which is a common technique in machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also discusses patch matching, person detection, and texture segmentation, which are all related to artificial intelligence and could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with Fourier series coefficients, which are commonly used in signal processing and could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
